The paper discusses the extended Burrows-Wheeler Transform (eBWT) and its application in detecting mutations in DNA fragments. This topic falls under the category of computational biology (cs.BIO) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of LCP arrays, which are commonly used in computational biology and bioinformatics.
